org.sd.text
Class RobinKarpStringSearch

java.lang.Object
  org.sd.text.RobinKarpStringSearch

public class RobinKarpStringSearch
extends java.lang.Object

Implementation of the Robin-Karp substring search algorithm.

This algorithm is good when multiple substrings are searched for within a string.

This implementation uses the NormalizedString abstraction.

Author:
Spence Koehler

search

public int[] search(java.lang.String string,
                    int acceptPartial)
Search the string for any of the substrings.

Parameters:
string - The normalized string to search.
acceptPartial - PatternFinder.ACCEPT_PARTIAL if a partial word match is ok; PatternFinder.FULL_WORD if an entire word (delineated by breaks on either side) must match; PatternFinder.BEGIN_WORD if a match must be found after a beginning break; PatternFinder.END_WORD if a match must be found ending with an end break.
Returns:
an array with the index of the first substring to match (at index 0), and its length (at index 1) or null.

Search the string for any of the substrings.
